news.title: About 4.8 lakh homes worth Rs 4.48 lakh crore stuck or delayed in top seven cities
news.para: For its research, Anarock has taken only those housing projects that were launched in 2014 or before across seven cities -- Delhi-NCR, Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Kolkata, Chennai, Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Pune.

news.title: Property mutation goes fully online, no manual process allowed now in Delhi
news.para: According to MCD, the certificate can be downloaded by the public on MCD’s website, which will be a QR code enabled computer-generated certificate requiring no signature.

news.title: No fee or Kolkata civic body permission needed for paint, repair job: Mayor
news.para: Hakim on Saturday told TOI that if anyone encountered harassment or were asked to pay money to carry out repairs of their houses, either internal or external, they could contact him.

news.title: Kolkata: Extra 'floor area ratio' hope for Bowbazar buildings
news.para: ​Mayor Firhad Hakim on Saturday said efforts were on to offer extra floor area ratio (FAR) at the time of reconstruction to those residents of Durga Pithuri Lane whose houses would need to be demolished.

news.title: Kanpur development body carries out demolition drive against illegal construction
news.para: The KDA demolished the illegal construction being carried out in premises no.01-Part 112/08-A Benjhabar owned by Ishtiaq Ahmad who had got sanctioned the building plan for residential purposes but raised the building for commercial purposes.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP to check residences converted into commercial set-ups
news.para: ​In Bengaluru, it is common for many residences to be converted as hotels, shops or any commercial establishments. Now, this civic agency has decided to set up squads to check these places so that property tax can be extracted.

news.title: Rights of construction workers are only on paper: Experts
news.para: Experts say the safety of workers at construction sites is often ignored because contractors find it is easier to pay some negotiated amount to the families of the deceased in such cases than to incur a recurring cost of overhauling and modernising their facilities.

news.title: Noida authority identifies 1,000 illegal farmhouses
news.para: Over the past three months, the authority has demolished as many as 90 farmhouses on the floodplains. Of these, 62 were brought down on June 1 alone in the Tilwara and Gulavali villages near Sector 150.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM launches TNUHDB flats for BPL families
news.para: 768 housing units at 65.6 crore were commissioned for below poverty line families in the two districts.

news.title: Kolkata civic body set to raze 10 vulnerable Bowbazar buildings
news.para: These buildings are included in the list of 27 buildings that have been earmarked as “vulnerable” by a team of experts from Jadavpur University after the subsidence occurred on Durga Pithuri Lane.

news.title: Relief for Maharashtra RERA chairman in benami case
news.para: The AA has said that the flat was “bought for adequate consideration before the show-cause notice was issued against him (Mehta) by the Income Tax department.”

news.title: Hisar: Stir over illegal occupation of plots for poor families
news.para: Following the dharna on Friday, the SDM wrote a letter to the Hisar DC, urging him to appoint a duty magistrate to carry out a survey on June 13 instead of June 20.

news.title: Compensation amount for property acquired for bullet train project not taxable: Bombay HC
news.para: ​A division bench of Justices S V Gangapurwala and M G Sewlikar passed its order on Thursday, on a petition filed by one Seema Patil, who sought a refund of the income tax deducted at the source by the NHSRCL after it acquired her property at Bhiwandi in Thane district for the project.

news.title: NMRC reviews plan for Noida Sec 142-Botanical Garden metro stretch
news.para: A review meeting was held here on Thursday under the chairmanship of NMRC's Managing Director Ritu Maheshwari to discuss issues related to the metro rail service.

news.title: Delhi Metro Rail Corporation seeks bank loan of Rs 2,700 crore for Express Line
news.para: According to sources, DMRC has written to these banks, proposing to raise the loan for purchase of “Airport Express Line assets”, and the banks willing to extend the loan have been requested to submit their bid. Sources said the loan amount would be used to pay Reliance Infra subsidiary Delhi Airport Metro Express Private Limited (DAMEPL).
